    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "description": {
      "content": "Jenkins exposes a machine-consumable Remote Access API for nearly every resource it manages. The API is accessed by appending /api/ to any Jenkins resource URL (top-level Jenkins, jobs, builds, queue, computers, views). The API supports XML (with XPath filtering), JSON (with JSONP), and a Python-compatible variant. HTTP Basic authentication with API tokens is used for authenticated requests, and the X-Jenkins response header advertises the Jenkins version.\n\nContact Support:\n Name: Jenkins Project",
